AU  - Card, David
T1  - Time Series Representations of Economic Variables and Alternative Models of the Labour Market
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/12/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297188
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 49
IS  - 5
SP  - 761
EP  - 782
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Accepting the hypothesis that the time-series “facts” of the aggregate labour market may be summarized by the linear autoregressive and moving average representations of wages, prices, unemployment, and interest rates implies that a useful theory ought to lead to predictions about these representations. Following this approach, this paper first catalogues many of the time-series facts about the aggregate labour market and then compares them against alternative models of the labour market based on the intertemporal substitution and staggered contract hypotheses.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297188
ER  - 



